name: Identity
description:
"There was a time when I hate my roots, I hate all about Chinese, I just wanted to be Indonesian. But then I realize, it's something i can't get rid off. It is part of me and who I am. 

Almost two years ago, I started learning about Chinese history, cultures, everything. I finally feel that sense of belonging, and I love the feeling of learning that."

—Aurelia Vizal

The piece is a part of "Fragmented Self" series.
The muse painted is Aurelia Vizel herself. The piece depict Chinese-Indonesian identity fragments in contemporary era.

Oil Digital Painting
PNG 4000 x 6000 px
